Reviewing NAPCO Security Technologies (NSSC) and Allegion PLC (ALLE)

					Posted by Sally Masters on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 



NAPCO Security Technologies (NASDAQ: NSSC) and Allegion PLC (NYSE:ALLE) are both industrial products companies, but which is the better investment? We will contrast the two companies based on the strength of their dividends, institutional ownership, earnings, valuation, profitabiliy, analyst recommendations and risk. 
Analyst Recommendations


 Get NAPCO Security Technologies Inc. alerts:



This is a breakdown of current ratings and recommmendations for NAPCO Security Technologies and Allegion PLC, as reported by MarketBeat.com. 



Sell Ratings
Hold Ratings
Buy Ratings
Strong Buy Ratings
Rating Score


NAPCO Security Technologies
0
1
2
0
2.67


Allegion PLC
0
2
4
0
2.67






NAPCO Security Technologies presently has a consensus target price of $8.75, suggesting a potential downside of 7.89%. Allegion PLC has a consensus target price of $84.75, suggesting a potential upside of 5.02%. Given Allegion PLC’s  higher possible upside, analysts plainly believe Allegion PLC is more favorable than NAPCO Security Technologies.
Institutional and Insider Ownership
23.5% of NAPCO Security Technologies shares are owned by institutional investors. Comparatively, 90.7% of Allegion PLC shares are owned by institutional investors. 37.8% of NAPCO Security Technologies shares are owned by company insiders. Comparatively, 0.6% of Allegion PLC shares are owned by company insiders. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that large money managers, endowments and hedge funds believe a stock is poised for long-term growth.
Profitability
This table compares NAPCO Security Technologies and Allegion PLC’s net margins, return on equity and return on assets.



